cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object detection in images. The use of deep reinforcement learning also suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The hierarchical approach to object detection could also place it in the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks and deep learning techniques could also suggest that it belongs to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
